      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:3:77:2",
      "text": [
        " السُّنَّةُ فِي الْإِحْرَامِ تَقْلِيمُ الْأَظْفَارِ وَ أَخْذُ الشَّارِبِ وَ حَلْقُ الْعَانَةِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali, from his father, from Hammad, from Hareyz, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The Sunnah regarding the <span class=\"iTxt\">Ihraam</span> is the clipping of the nails, and taking off the moustache, and shaving the pubic area’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Ali has narrated from his father from Hammad from Hariz who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Of the Sunnah in Ihram is to trim finger nails, mustache and pubic hairs.’” "
        ]
      }
